properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 1 at 1:57PM AKST until February 3 at 12:00AM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow expected. Plan on areas of poor visibilities
and slick roadways to create difficult travel conditions at
times. Winds gusting as high as 60 mph will cause areas of
blowing and drifting snow.

* WHERE...Eastern Alaska Range.

* WHEN...Until midnight Sunday night.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds gusting as high as 60 mph will cause
areas of blowing and drifting snow. Cold wind chills as low as
45 below zero will cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to
exposed skin.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for blowing snow means periods of
blowing snow will cause travel difficulties. The latest road
conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT AKST SUNDAY NIGHT... ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IS CANCELLED
